## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 904(a)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) caps the foreign tax credit at the U.S. tax on foreign-source taxable income, computed as a fraction of total U.S. tax: `limit = regular_tax × (foreign-source taxable income ÷ total taxable income)`. The cap applies separately to each FTC basket. Foreign tax paid above the cap doesn't generate a credit this year but can carry forward (§ 904(c)).

